2026-04-06 Bootstrap project plan, product spec, README, and AGENTS guidance for the initial TermiWeb implementation.
2026-04-06 Scaffolded the first working TermiWeb app with shared workspace tabs, cookie auth, mobile terminal controls, local tests, and a production build path.
2026-04-06 Hardened shell resolution to prefer the default PowerShell 7 install path before PATH-based fallback behavior.
2026-04-06 Updated shell resolution precedence so PowerShell 7 from PATH wins, with the default install path used as a fallback before Windows PowerShell.
2026-04-06 Changed the default TermiWeb web port from 4317 to 22443 to avoid common telemetry-port collisions and match the preferred app identity.
2026-04-06 Added repo-root .env loading and fixed LAN host resolution so TERMIWEB_ALLOW_LAN=true works with the sample config.
2026-04-06 Refined the browser UI with clearer host identity, instance terminology, a collapsible instance rail, and a keyboard-style arrow cluster for mobile controls.
2026-04-06 Added shared-active-instance metadata, a select mode for copying terminal text, home-directory shell starts, and icon-based refresh/collapse controls.
2026-04-06 Made LAN binding the default path, added a fixed 120-column terminal width, swapped the rail icons, and exposed a Del key for mobile control.
2026-04-06 Stopped cross-device instance auto-following, made sidebar collapse local to each browser, switched select mode to a rendered viewport snapshot, narrowed the collapsed rail and control cluster, and changed the shared terminal width default to 40 columns.
2026-04-06 Removed the separate mobile layout in favor of one shared cross-device layout, doubled the main control density per row, separated collapsed instance close buttons from card hit targets, and changed the shared terminal width default to 80 columns.
2026-04-06 Removed page-level forced workspace width so phones fit the UI to the viewport again, while keeping zoom enabled and leaving overflow localized to the terminal surface.
2026-04-06 Switched the default viewport metadata to a desktop-style layout width so phones behave more like "Desktop Site" mode without requiring a per-device browser toggle.
2026-04-06 Removed the forced `initial-scale=1.0` from the desktop-style mobile viewport so browsers can choose a more zoomed-out initial fit on their own.
2026-04-06 Added `Home` and `End` to the compact mobile key cluster and placed them above the left and right arrow keys.
2026-04-06 Reworked `Ctrl` and `Alt` so a single tap arms the next key, a double tap locks the modifier, and the buttons visibly distinguish armed and locked states.
2026-04-06 Merged the terminal header into the main header, moved the terminal workspace into a top-aligned 4:3-aware stage, kept the sidebar outside the scaled stage, and defaulted the sidebar to collapsed on narrow viewports when no local preference exists.
2026-04-06 Moved the keyboard control tray out of the scaled workspace stage so the terminal buttons stay finger-sized on phones.
2026-04-06 Changed terminal sizing so 80 columns fit the available width while rows stay elastic, and aligned the cursor-key cluster beside the main control rows.
2026-04-06 Expanded the control tray into three taller main-button rows and matched the non-arrow button height to the cursor-key buttons for better touch targets.
2026-04-06 Changed the 4:3 stage behavior to keep full width and trim height instead of scaling the entire workspace down on narrow viewports.
2026-04-06 Tied the workspace shell to the live visual viewport height so the control tray stays above the on-screen keyboard on phones.
2026-04-06 Moved the control tray inside the outer terminal shell and reordered the main keys to Esc/Bksp/Del, Tab/Select/Copy, and Ctrl/Alt/Paste with Enter under the cursor cluster.
2026-04-06 Reused the lowest available auto-generated instance number, normalized legacy Terminal-style instance names forward to Instance naming, and enlarged the instance rail targets.
2026-04-06 Stacked the collapsed rail actions vertically so the collapse toggle sits above refresh instead of beside it.
2026-04-06 Added a findings log for dogfood issues and updated the repo workflow/docs to batch polish work from recorded findings.
2026-04-06 Fixed the first findings batch by making on-screen navigation keys application-cursor aware, stabilizing touch control focus and viewport refits, switching to a single solid terminal cursor, and auto-seeding Instance 1 when a login reaches an empty workspace.
2026-04-06 Tightened the first findings batch by giving on-screen Home and End a fallback sequence path and by reapplying the fitted desktop-style mobile viewport scale after orientation changes.
2026-04-06 Replaced the restart-time websocket reconnect flap with server recovery polling so live pages wait for the server and refresh themselves once it is back.
2026-04-06 Moved the control tray off synthetic mobile click handling onto direct touch/pointer activation, and increased the control tray key height while keeping the cursor cluster square.
2026-04-07 Reframed the docs around TermiWeb as a workstation-first tool, added deployment-philosophy guidance for trusted-network defaults plus operator-managed remote deployments, and aligned the 0.1 specs with that direction without claiming unshipped features.
2026-04-07 Corrected the deployment docs so careful WAN exposure is treated as a legitimate advanced TermiWeb use case, while keeping the trusted-network default and the current 0.1 security boundaries explicit.
2026-04-07 Added a collapsible keyboard control tray with a per-browser preference so users can trade control-panel space for more visible terminal rows.
2026-04-07 Added hidden Windows background start/restart scripts so TermiWeb can be launched without spawning an extra empty console window.
2026-04-07 Moved the keyboard-tray collapse handle onto the seam between the terminal and tray so it no longer spends a dedicated header row.
2026-04-07 Documented an isolated single-tab Browser Session as a possible `0.2` instance type, without committing to Brave-profile or sync integration.
2026-04-08 Documented per-instance column width as the next 0.1 feature, with `80` as the new-instance default and a topbar shared-session control for changing width.
2026-04-08 Added an explicit 0.1 release standard, linked it from the plan and README, and called out interactive CLI rendering drift as the main known gap against that release bar.
2026-04-08 Added dated milestones through M7 in the project plan, including 0.1 release polish, a GitHub Pages download site, and a later marketing phase while keeping TermiWeb open source and free to use.
2026-04-08 Inserted a dedicated installer-experience milestone into the roadmap and shifted the release-site and marketing milestones out by one week.
2026-04-08 Added a visible `0.1` version badge to the login and main workspace UI, sourced from the package version so the running build is obvious before and after login.
2026-04-08 Removed the instance-card exit-status caption so cards no longer show the awkward "Fresh shell when opened" copy.
2026-04-08 Disabled autocorrect, autocapitalize, spellcheck, and Grammarly-style text assistance on the live terminal input so mobile keyboards stop trying to reinterpret commands.
2026-04-08 Hid the dead outer terminal scrollbar, widened the real xterm scrollbar for touch devices, and added one-finger touch scrolling on the visible terminal surface for mobile scrollback.
2026-04-08 Switched terminal touch scrolling to xterm's real scroll model, hid the native xterm viewport scrollbar, and enlarged the custom scrollbar thumb for better mobile dragging.
2026-04-09 Shipped per-instance shared column width with a topbar `Cols N` control, preset/custom widths, shared-session confirmation, persisted width metadata, and layout rules that preserve the existing scaling model around the chosen column count.
2026-04-09 Raised the top bar above the workspace stack so the shared-width popover opens in front of the sidebar and terminal instead of behind them.
2026-04-09 Replaced the shared-width popover's `132`-column preset with `160`.
2026-04-09 Removed the global 4:3 workspace-stage cap so the terminal can use the full available height and recover rows that were being discarded before xterm fit calculations.
2026-04-09 Added a focused `0.1` spec for restart-stable shared-password sessions so recovery refreshes can preserve login state across normal server restarts.
2026-04-09 Persisted shared-password browser sessions under `.termiweb/` so automatic refresh after a normal server restart no longer forces a fresh login when the cookie is still valid.
2026-04-09 Replaced `shared-password` wording in the docs with `configured app password` or `authenticated session` so the language matches the actual access model without implying password-sharing as a practice.
2026-04-09 Clarified the terminal width-fit spec so configured columns must always fit inside the visible `xterm` viewport width, with font sizing owning width fit and rows then flowing from height.
2026-04-09 Simplified terminal width fitting to use xterm's own proposed column fit, made the xterm root fill the available width directly, and removed the older visible-width heuristics from the font-sizing path.
2026-04-09 Lowered the width-fit floor to `6px` and added a terminal-local horizontal scrollbar fallback for cases where the configured columns still cannot fit without clipping.
2026-04-09 Lowered the websocket/client protocol minimum row count from `5` to `1` so mobile viewport churn and tiny-height terminal states no longer throw resize validation errors.
2026-04-09 Replaced the responsive expanded sidebar width with a fixed `16.5rem` rail so the instance panel stops resizing as aggressively with the viewport.
2026-04-09 Split the instance status pill and the New instance action onto their own rows so the sidebar rail reads more cleanly and wraps less aggressively.
2026-04-09 Joined each instance card and its close button into a single seam-aligned control in both expanded and collapsed sidebar layouts.
2026-04-09 Restored the collapsed instance card's top-right corner radius and changed the close glyph to a darker red for clearer visual separation.
2026-04-09 Enlarged the instance close glyph, returned it to white, and gave the close control a soft red border/background treatment instead of the default neutral or accent styling.
2026-04-09 Removed the shared seam border between each instance card and its close control in both expanded and collapsed sidebar layouts.
2026-04-09 Removed the redundant sidebar eyebrow so the interface now shows only one `Instances` label in the side panel header.
2026-04-09 Switched the instance-card seam to true zero-width contacting borders instead of transparent-edge and overlap tricks in both expanded and collapsed sidebar layouts.
2026-04-09 Restored the collapsed instance card's right outer border and the close control's left outer border so the stacked layout keeps its full outside frame while the shared seam stays borderless.
2026-04-09 Changed collapsed auto-named instance labels to show only their number and removed the collapsed-mode small-font override so those labels keep the expanded title size.
2026-04-09 Made collapsed-instance labels update immediately when the sidebar toggles and removed the ambiguous live-process note from the sidebar helper copy.
2026-04-09 Wrapped hostname and address together inside a single host pill in both headers and converted the version from a pill badge to plain secondary text.
2026-04-09 Increased host pill padding and host/address text sizes, and restyled the `Cols` control as a clearer dropdown-style action with stronger button affordance and a caret.
2026-04-09 Removed the gap between the product name and version so the mixed-font wordmark reads as a single unit in both headers.
2026-04-09 Increased the host pill to a materially wider shared padding in both headers so the hostname/address chip reads with clear horizontal breathing room.
2026-04-09 Restored the host pill's original vertical padding while keeping the wider horizontal padding so the chip reads broader without getting taller.
2026-04-09 Increased the host pill's horizontal padding substantially in both headers so the hostname/address chip has clearly visible side breathing room without growing taller.
2026-04-09 Replaced the previous host-pill padding workaround with real horizontal margin in both headers and returned the internal spacing to a saner level.
2026-04-09 Doubled the host pill's real horizontal margin in both headers for much stronger left/right separation from surrounding header content.
2026-04-09 Set the version label to the `small` font size in both headers so it reads as quieter secondary metadata.
2026-04-09 Increased general UI typography by 50 percent outside the terminal and cursor cluster, moved the host pill back under the branding without side margins, and made the sidebar forcibly auto-collapse below 800px.
2026-04-09 Tightened the keyboard tray toggle metrics, put the sidebar title and collapse button on the same row with refresh on its own right-aligned row, restored status-pill text to its pre-scale size, converted session metadata to two stacked lines, and widened the session area relative to the branding block.
2026-04-09 Replaced the bad `topbar-session` width hack with a saner topbar grid split and restyled the focus/logout controls as clearer action buttons with emoji labels instead of pill-like chips.
2026-04-10 Separated topbar status pills from action buttons into distinct groups and made the collapsed tray toggle use top padding instead of bottom padding.
2026-04-10 Coalesced mobile viewport churn into a settled shared terminal resize, removed visual-viewport scroll resize spam, and added in-session snapshot resync after disruptive viewport changes and width changes so the terminal can recover without a full page refresh.
2026-04-10 Changed restart semantics to return to one fresh active `Instance 1` instead of restoring dead instances, and made live PTY row resizing grow-only so smaller devices and transient mobile viewport changes do not rewrite shared terminal history downward.
2026-04-10 Simplified phone rotation further by removing runtime viewport-meta rewriting and orientation choreography, using local snapshot resync instead of session reattach for coarse-pointer viewport changes, and hiding the manual sidebar-collapse toggle when narrow width forces the sidebar collapsed.
2026-04-10 Moved the terminal `Type` action into the sidebar so it remains available in expanded and collapsed rail states, and hardened terminal input attributes with stricter no-assistance hints for mobile keyboards.
2026-04-10 Moved the shared columns control out of the topbar and onto the active instance, added a dedicated vertically scrollable instances rail, and tightened the instance-row join so the close control reads as part of the same widget.
2026-04-10 Simplified live resize behavior so viewport changes stay local after shell startup, kept live PTY rows stable across later device resizes, moved the collapsed `Cols` control into the joined instance widget, and fixed stale auto-instance numbering to ignore outdated counters.
2026-04-10 Refined the active-instance `Columns` control into a joined lower segment in expanded view, tightened collapsed-width behavior by removing idle scrollbar gutter reservation, and brought the `Cols` flyout closer to its launching control with a higher overlay priority.
